Candlepin is a service which allows companies to manage software
subscriptions. The subscriptions allow users to access
content provided by those subscriptions over secure connections.

The server exposes functionality over a REST API, and stores data
in a backend SQL database. The source code is delivered under the
GPL. See LICENSE for explicit version information.

More information on the service can be found at
https://fedorahosted.org/candlepin/. Questions can be sent to the
mailing list at https://lists.fedorahosted.org/mailman/listinfo/candlepin
or on Freenode at #candlepin.
